{
  "id": "L24",
  "title": "Leaving a Voicemail Message",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you'll learn how to leave a clear voicemail message in Dutch. Let's start with introducing yourself."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L24_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hallo",
        "meaning": "Hello"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L24_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Mijn naam is...",
        "meaning": "My name is..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L24_V01",
      "data": {
        "Het adres": "The address"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L24_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Mijn adres is...",
        "meaning": "My address is..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Spelling your name can be important. The Dutch alphabet is similar to English, but the pronunciation of letters is different."
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L24_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "S",
        "phonetic": "/ɛs/",
        "tip": "Sounds like the English letter 'S'"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L24_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "M",
        "phonetic": "/ɛm/",
        "tip": "Sounds like the English letter 'M'"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L24_P03",
      "data": {
        "word": "I",
        "phonetic": "/i/",
        "tip": "Sounds like the 'ee' in 'see'"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L24_P04",
      "data": {
        "word": "T",
        "phonetic": "/teː/",
        "tip": "Sounds like 'tay'"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L24_P05",
      "data": {
        "word": "H",
        "phonetic": "/ɦaː/",
        "tip": "A soft 'h' sound, like a sigh"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L24_S01",
      "title": "Introduction and Identification",
      "setting": "You are calling the housing agency, but nobody answers. You will now leave a voicemail message, part by part.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Start your message",
          "chatbot_message": "Hallo. Dit is de voicemail. Spreek na de piep. *piep*"
        },
        {
          "title": "Greet and state your name",
          "chatbot_message": "...",
          "extract_info": {
            "user_name": "Extract the user's full name"
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "State your address",
          "chatbot_message": "..."
        },
        {
          "title": "Spell your last name",
          "chatbot_message": "..."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Good. Now, let's explain the reason for your call. Be clear and simple."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L24_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik bel voor...",
        "meaning": "I am calling about..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L24_V02",
      "data": {
        "de verwarming": "the heating"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L24_V03",
      "data": {
        "werkt niet": "is not working"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "You can combine words to form a sentence. For example: 'Ik bel voor de verwarming. De verwarming werkt niet'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L24_V04",
      "data": {
        "sinds": "since"
      }
    },
    {
